          "email": "jian.yu@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-11-17 07:08:37.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9771 ldlm: fix the issues introduced by try bits",
        "message": "LU-9771 ldlm: fix the issues introduced by try bits\n\nldlm_process_inode_bits_lock() should take the try bits in the\nwaiting list into consideration. If there is a lock in the waiting\nlist having try_bits conflicted with the requested lock, the try_bits\nof that lock should be cleared.\n\nOther improvements in this patch are to grant try_bits in atomic, and\nmdt_object_lock_try() should never return negative for try lock only,\nand code cleanups.\n\nSigned-off-by: Jinshan Xiong <jinshan.xiong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ia9f6ec48d3ef9ac831d0e067b1bb9acfa2a64607\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/flr"
    }
  },
